    <text id="F4012T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McClure writes to Slifer requesting details regarding certain claims made for
                    damages after a Confederate raid. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>McClure &amp; Stoner<lb/>Editors and Proprietors.<lb/>Franklin Repository
                    Office,<lb/>Chambersburg, Pa. <name type="recipient"/>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-02-03"><abbr expan="February">Feb</abbr> 3, 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg, <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Pa.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The Commissioner <unclear>apportio</unclear> to appraise damages caused by the
                    Rebel Raid has made a report to the <abbr expan="committee">Cmt</abbr> of
                    Dauphin County, which when acted upon, will <unclear>go</unclear> to the <orig
                        reg="Governor">Govenor</orig>.</p>

                <p>I presume it was acted on about the 18th <unclear>alt</unclear>, &amp; is
                    with the <abbr expan="Governor">Gv</abbr> now.</p>

                <p>Please instruct me of the checks to copy it - I mean just the names &amp;
                    amount awarded - for me so that I can get it the last of this week or
                        <unclear>bring</unclear> it next for the publication.</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <p>I will pay the check <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> may do it <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> of him for the
                    work. It will be of special interest to the people in this
                    <unclear>section</unclear></p>

                <p>I do not want any of the testimony, of course - just the awards,
                    <unclear>giving</unclear> the names, number of <unclear>house</unclear>
                    &amp; <abbr expan="amount">amt</abbr>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours</salute>
                    <signed>AKMcClure</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr> Eli Slifer</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
